# Target samples

One configuration sample per target type. Each file is a single target object you can copy into the
`targets` array of a run configuration. `all-targets.json` holds every target in one array.

Set `enabled` to `true` for the targets you want, fill in the placeholder property values, and confirm
the identity has the role the target requires. See [Targets](../../docs/guides/targets.md) for the
properties each target reads and the authentication model.

